A passenger on the ICE train tweeted a picture of the shattered windows and said: “Just got on the intercity ICE train. Shattered windows. Passengers say they think they were hit with bullets.”

@SueddeutscheBahn Just got on the Intercity ICE train (Bahn 909). Shattered windows. Passenger say they think it was hit with bullets — Christian H. (@CH_R_H) October 3, 2016

According to the Sueddeutsche, the train’s windows were shot out with a “small caliber” weapon.

Another passenger tweeted a picture showing a police escort, which has since been removed.

@CH_R-H @SueddeutschBahn @Suedzeitung just checked the ICE. A police escort has arrived, the situation seems under control — Rene-Marcel Bätzing (@RenMarcel_B) October 3 2016
